<%# Phase 27 §01c — Collections shelf.
    Top-of-page horizontal shelf listing every Collection, alphabetical
    (case-insensitive). Each tile navigates to `/games?collection=<slug>`
    so the existing controller filter narrows the listing below; once
    01b lands its filter row, the same URL is the chip-state hand-off.

    Tiles render at the `:shelf` cover-art size (50% of the standard
    150x200 grid tile, locked by master for 01c — fall back to 65-70%
    if covers look unreadable per the addendum). Collections curate
    Games so the tile can in principle show a representative cover; the
    Collection model has no first-class cover field yet, so the tile is
    a bracketed legend over a neutral cover block (matches the Genres
    shelf above).

    Note: the spec mentions filtering Collections by a `kind: :custom` /
    `custom: true` flag (open question #2). The Collection schema in
    Phase 14 has no such column, so this shelf surfaces every
    Collection. The filter can be reintroduced once that column ships.

    Locals:
      collections  ActiveRecord::Relation of Collection rows, pre-
                   ordered by caller (controller passes alphabetical
                   case-insensitive).
%>
<%
  collections = local_assigns.fetch(:collections)
%>
<section class="shelf shelf--collections" style="margin-top: 12px;" data-controller="steam-shelf">
  <div class="dot-list" style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
    <h2 style="margin: 0;">collections</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="shelf-row" data-steam-shelf-target="row"
       style="display: flex; gap: 6px; overflow-x: auto; padding-bottom: 6px;">
    <% if collections.any? %>
      <% collections.each do |collection| %>
        <%
          href = if collection.slug.present?
                   games_path(collection: collection.slug)
                 else
                   games_path(collection: collection.id)
                 end
        %>
        <a href="<%= href %>"
           class="tile tile--shelf"
           style="flex: 0 0 75px; width: 75px; display: block; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; cursor: pointer;"
           data-tile-collection-id="<%= collection.id %>"
           data-tile-variant="shelf"
           title="<%= collection.name %>">
          <div class="tile-cover" style="width: 75px; height: 100px; overflow: hidden; background: #f6f6f6; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border: 1px solid #ddd;">
            <span class="text-muted" style="font-size: 10px;">[<%= collection.name.to_s.downcase %>]</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tile-caption" style="padding: 4px 0; font-size: 10px; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;">
            <%= collection.name %>
          </div>
        </a>
      <% end %>
    <% else %>
      <p class="text-muted" style="margin: 0; font-size: 11px;">(no collections yet)</p>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</section>
